  "setupGuideLinkIntro": "Don't have a configuration? Create your congregation's own free database:",
  "setupGuideLinkButton": "How to set up a new congregation",
  "setupGuideTitle": "Set up a new congregation",
  "setupGuideIntro": "This app is self-hosted: your congregation's data lives in your own free Google Firebase project that nobody else can access. Setting it up takes about 15 minutes and requires no programming — all you need is a Google account. Follow the steps below on this phone or on a computer.",
  "setupGuideOpenConsole": "Open Firebase console",
  "setupGuideStep1Title": "Create a Firebase project",
  "setupGuideStep1Body1": "Open console.firebase.google.com, sign in with your Google account and tap \"Get started by setting up a Firebase project\".",
  "setupGuideStep1Body2": "Name the project, e.g. \"congregation-mytown\", accept the terms and continue. If Google Analytics is offered, disable it — it is not needed. Stay on the free Spark plan; the app is designed to never need billing.",
  "setupGuideStep2Title": "Enable e-mail sign-in",
  "setupGuideStep2Body1": "In the left menu choose Security → Authentication.",
  "setupGuideStep2Body2": "Tap \"Get started\".",
  "setupGuideStep2Body3": "On the \"Sign-in method\" tab choose Email/Password.",
  "setupGuideStep2Body4": "Enable the first toggle (leave \"Email link\" off) and tap Save.",
  "setupGuideStep3Title": "Create the Firestore database",
  "setupGuideStep3Body1": "In the left menu choose Databases & Storage → Firestore.",
  "setupGuideStep3Body2": "Tap \"Create database\".",
  "setupGuideStep3Body3": "Choose the Standard edition.",
  "setupGuideStep3Body4": "Choose a location close to you (e.g. europe-west3 for Central Europe). It cannot be changed later.",
  "setupGuideStep3Body5": "Start in production mode…",
  "setupGuideStep3Body6": "…and tap Create.",
  "setupGuideStep4Title": "Install the security rules",
  "setupGuideStep4Body1": "The rules decide who may read and write which data (e.g. only verified publishers can see schedules). In the Firestore database open the Rules tab and tap \"Edit rules\".",
  "setupGuideStep4Body2": "Delete everything in the editor and paste the copied rules.",
  "setupGuideStep4Body3": "Tap Publish.",
  "setupGuideStep4Note": "Repeat this step whenever a new app version ships updated rules.",
  "setupGuideStep5Title": "Get the app configuration",
  "setupGuideStep5Body1": "Tap the gear icon next to \"Project Overview\" (top left) and choose Project settings.",
  "setupGuideStep5Body2": "On the General tab scroll down to \"Your apps\" and tap the web icon </>.",
  "setupGuideStep5Body3": "Enter a nickname, e.g. \"congregation-app\", leave hosting off and tap \"Register app\".",
  "setupGuideStep5Body4": "A code block with \"const firebaseConfig = …\" appears. Select and copy just the configuration between the curly braces — including the braces themselves.",
  "setupGuideStep5Note": "This configuration is not a secret — it only identifies your project. The data is protected by the security rules from step 4.",
  "setupGuideRulesTitle": "Security rules (firestore.rules)",
  "setupGuideRulesCopy": "Copy rules",
  "setupGuideRulesCopied": "Rules copied to clipboard.",
  "setupGuideRulesView": "Show rules text",
  "setupGuideRulesLoadError": "Could not load the rules text.",
  "setupGuideFinish": "Done! Go back, paste the copied configuration and tap Connect. Then choose \"Set up a new congregation\" and register as the first administrator.",
  "setupGuideBackToConnect": "Back to the connection screen",

